newsitem.title: SWITZERLAND: Swiss launch three-month money market claims.
newsitem.headline: Swiss launch three-month money market claims.

text.p: The Swiss federal government is issuing three-month money market claims to be paid for on October 17, the Swiss National Bank said.
The allocation follows the end of subscriptions on October 15.
The previous issue of three-month claims, paid for on October 10, raised 913.85 million francs and was priced at 99.667 percent to yield 1.332 percent annually.
